# Time-Curvature Gravity Model

## Concept

Gravity is modeled as an outcome of dynamic curvature in space-time-energy fields, changing over time.

## Key Equation

Φ(r, t) = - G * M / (r + α * f(t))

Where:
- Φ = gravitational potential
- G = gravitational constant
- M = mass of Earth
- r = radial distance from axis
- α = curvature coefficient
- f(t) = time-based curvature function

## Relationship to General Relativity

In this model, instead of static curvature, we allow curvature to evolve locally and globally over time, adapting to:
- solar energy inputs
- rotational strain
- mass-energy field variations
